label: Specimen of biological sex role
definition: A role that inheres in a specimen organism and is realised in some investigation process based on the actual or estimated biological sex of the bearer.
example of usage: The role a skeletal specimen takes on in an investigation that estimates age at death based on the outcome of a previous estimation of biological sex.

label: Female specimen role
definition: A role that inheres in a specimen that either has female sex or is assumed to do so and which is realised in an investigation it participates in based on its biological sex.

label: Specimen of indeterminate sex role
definition: A role that inheres in a specimen for which biological sex cannot be determined or for which sex estimation has not yielded any conclusive result and which is realised in an investigation it participates in based on its biological sex.

label: Male specimen role
definition: A role that inheres in a specimen that either has male sex or is assumed to do so and which is realised in an investigation it participates in based on its biological sex.
